WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:01.453
J: I just wanted to say
that I didn't see anything

00:01.515 --> 00:03.444
the other day... in the bathroom.

00:03.446 --> 00:05.053
I don't know what you're talking about.

00:05.055 --> 00:08.553
Smurf: Deran feels
terrible about what he did.

00:08.656 --> 00:10.984
Catherine: A security guard died,
and he wasn't just a security guard...

00:10.986 --> 00:12.892
he was a real cop.

00:12.931 --> 00:14.693
Do you know who my dad is?

00:14.748 --> 00:18.591
There was only one that she really loved.

00:18.645 --> 00:21.181
Was it Baz?

00:21.333 --> 00:23.057
Catherine: You kidnapped my child.

00:23.127 --> 00:26.565
Smurf: Your child was wandering
around a grocery store all by herself.

00:26.635 --> 00:29.005
You're lucky she wasn't
<i>really</i> kidnapped.

00:29.068 --> 00:31.174
What kind of family do
you think we are, man?

00:31.244 --> 00:33.023
- Destroy the watches.
- Craig: What?!

00:33.086 --> 00:35.206
Pope: Where is it... the watch I gave you?

00:35.289 --> 00:36.678
J: I gave it to Nicky.

00:36.781 --> 00:38.253
Some of us gotta work to live.

00:38.300 --> 00:39.732
Parole agent's coming around,

00:39.734 --> 00:42.137
I'm not looking to take <i>any</i> risk.

00:42.195 --> 00:44.270
Smurf: Lie low. Don't
be stupid. We'll be okay.

00:44.348 --> 00:46.950
Baz: He said pulling off another
job is not gonna play so well.

00:47.005 --> 00:49.303
Feel like making some
money... old time's sake?

00:49.480 --> 00:50.783
What kind of money you talking?

00:50.814 --> 00:53.074
I can't just toss a
quarter key out the window.

00:53.121 --> 00:54.649
- Where is it?
- [Clears throat]

00:54.712 --> 00:56.241
It's fine. It's in the burrito.

00:56.287 --> 00:57.772
We made 8 grand!

00:57.795 --> 01:00.586
Smurf: We don't take stupid
risks. We're not greedy.

01:00.656 --> 01:02.648
Sometimes one of these rules gets broken.

01:02.703 --> 01:05.376
There are no secrets in this family...

01:05.543 --> 01:07.315
especially not from me.

01:07.889 --> 01:11.429
♪♪

01:11.526 --> 01:17.384
♪ She stares deeply ♪

01:17.431 --> 01:21.018
♪ Locked inside me ♪

01:21.214 --> 01:24.482
♪ Burnin' brightly ♪

01:27.189 --> 01:32.797
♪ One they know that I cannot take ♪

01:32.941 --> 01:36.167
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin ♪

01:36.339 --> 01:39.907
♪ Every night now, they'll win ♪

01:43.598 --> 01:46.043
♪ Come and meet my black hole ♪

01:46.098 --> 01:49.830
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:49.974 --> 01:53.951
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:53.953 --> 01:57.388
♪ I've got a big black hole ♪

01:57.707 --> 02:01.759
♪ I've got a big
black, big black hole ♪

02:01.761 --> 02:05.607
♪ Got a big black hole inside of me ♪

02:05.657 --> 02:07.931
♪ Got a ♪

02:15.189 --> 02:17.283
[Alarm clock beeping]

02:21.232 --> 02:23.222
[Beeping stops]

02:25.000 --> 02:31.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:36.590 --> 02:38.257
[Knock on door]

02:42.925 --> 02:45.177
I'm sorry for the pool.

02:45.193 --> 02:47.696
I was just screwing around, so...

02:48.773 --> 02:51.017
Oh, that's cool.

02:51.019 --> 02:53.085
[Clears throat]

02:53.178 --> 02:54.565
You want to take a swing at me?

02:54.597 --> 02:55.708
[Scoffs]

02:56.687 --> 02:58.186
No.

02:58.290 --> 03:00.352
Not gonna make the offer again.

03:06.500 --> 03:08.401
Do you know what that is?

03:11.876 --> 03:14.167
Is that Baz, Pope, Julia?

03:16.602 --> 03:19.845
Oh, I'm surprised Smurf
didn't sand that shit off, man.

03:22.638 --> 03:25.055
Smurf asks, we're cool, right?

03:25.952 --> 03:27.032
Yeah.

03:27.961 --> 03:29.460
Okay.

03:30.341 --> 03:31.873
[Sighs]

03:36.182 --> 03:37.715
When'd you get here?

03:37.801 --> 03:40.061
How the hell does this thing work?

03:40.923 --> 03:43.231
They didn't have espresso
machines at Folsom?

03:43.293 --> 03:44.258
I just want coffee.

03:44.296 --> 03:45.468
Okay.

03:49.910 --> 03:51.310
Where's breakfast?

03:51.312 --> 03:52.476
Smurf didn't make it.

03:52.511 --> 03:54.144
Yeah, no shit.

03:54.243 --> 03:56.128
Is Craig here?

03:56.195 --> 03:58.480
Uh, no, he spent the night at his place.

03:58.542 --> 04:00.418
- But he's still in for paintball.
- What?

04:00.483 --> 04:02.748
Paintball on your birthday... like always.

04:02.810 --> 04:04.401
No, I... no, thanks.

04:04.472 --> 04:06.826
Come on... you get to shoot
something without getting arrested.

04:06.881 --> 04:08.180
I thought you love paintball.

04:08.243 --> 04:10.031
Yeah, when I was 16.

04:10.094 --> 04:12.535
I don't know, man.

04:12.574 --> 04:13.392
We're also going skydiving

04:13.427 --> 04:14.672
- this afternoon, too.
- No. We're not.

04:14.719 --> 04:16.438
You've been staring at
bars for three years.

04:16.473 --> 04:17.202
Let's go have some fun. Come on.

04:17.237 --> 04:18.567
Besides, I already put the down payment

04:18.613 --> 04:20.406
on the plane, so you gotta go.

04:20.469 --> 04:22.217
- What plane?
- For Pope's birthday.

04:22.266 --> 04:24.397
Skydiving, paintball. We're
gonna take him out tonight.

04:24.432 --> 04:25.983
Celebrate the fact that
we don't have to go through

04:26.018 --> 04:28.516
a metal detector to bring
him his cake this year.

04:28.551 --> 04:30.216
Happy birthday, sweetie.

04:30.295 --> 04:32.627
[Refrigerator door opens, bottles clank]

04:32.662 --> 04:33.830
Sounds like a fun day.

04:33.865 --> 04:35.718
- Yeah, for <i>them.</i>
- What does that mean?

04:35.780 --> 04:37.166
It's all shit that <i>you</i> want to do.

04:37.201 --> 04:39.009
You love paintball, you like strip clubs,

04:39.044 --> 04:40.544
Craig likes jumping out of planes.

04:40.595 --> 04:43.028
All right, asshole, what
do <i>you</i> want to do?

04:47.801 --> 04:50.803
I'm gonna go catch a session
before the tide gets too high.

04:50.921 --> 04:52.554
Okay. [Smooches]

04:54.645 --> 04:56.045
Bye, baby.

04:57.551 --> 04:59.044
[Door opens]

04:59.046 --> 05:01.747
That's quite a lavish day you have planned.

05:01.749 --> 05:03.359
You need any money?

05:03.394 --> 05:04.501
No, we got it covered.

05:04.536 --> 05:05.738
Yeah, we pooled what we had,

05:05.785 --> 05:07.987
called in some favors, so we're good.

05:08.056 --> 05:09.341
Okay.

05:09.427 --> 05:12.405
I talked to J. It's all good.

05:21.358 --> 05:22.468
Smurf.

05:22.554 --> 05:24.170
Hey, I think we need to get back to work,

05:24.172 --> 05:25.804
talk about the next job, no?

05:25.839 --> 05:27.606
How's Lena?

05:27.608 --> 05:29.208
Uh, well, Cath has been sick,

05:29.210 --> 05:31.010
so that's why she hasn't brought her over.

05:31.012 --> 05:32.458
- Morning, sweetie.
- Morning.

05:32.493 --> 05:34.280
- She's been sick?
- Yeah.

05:34.391 --> 05:35.648
Well, I would have gone over and helped her

05:35.683 --> 05:38.676
take care of the baby if she called.

05:38.711 --> 05:40.141
[Chuckles]

05:40.789 --> 05:42.523
Come on, Smurf. You took her kid.

05:42.558 --> 05:44.957
She has every right to be pissed.

05:44.959 --> 05:47.426
Tell her I hope she feels better.

05:56.507 --> 05:58.671
You're still so shy.

05:58.829 --> 06:03.642
I changed your diapers every day, baby.

06:03.644 --> 06:06.145
Go on. I won't look.

06:15.288 --> 06:19.658
Hey, sweetie, do you need anything?

06:19.660 --> 06:21.727
Maybe some money?

06:21.729 --> 06:23.128
No.

06:24.664 --> 06:26.165
Hmm?

06:26.284 --> 06:28.000
Don't tell your uncles.

06:29.124 --> 06:31.842
They've been on me for cash for weeks.

06:31.943 --> 06:35.774
And now they have this
big birthday plan for Pope.

06:35.961 --> 06:37.695
How do you think they'll manage that?

06:37.730 --> 06:40.177
They haven't asked me for any money.

06:41.163 --> 06:42.261
I'm not sure.

06:42.359 --> 06:44.550
You haven't heard
anything around the house,

06:44.645 --> 06:46.381
boys talking or anything?

06:46.416 --> 06:47.896
Nope.

06:50.461 --> 06:53.010
I'll show you a thing
or two about paintball.

06:53.087 --> 06:54.317
Pope: Yeah, like you know.

06:54.352 --> 06:55.781
Yeah, I do.

07:01.330 --> 07:04.471
I'm going out to pick
some things up for tonight.

07:05.600 --> 07:10.703
If I find one speck of paint
on this house, God help you.

07:10.738 --> 07:12.771
[Rock music plays]

07:20.320 --> 07:23.535
♪ Oh, baby, I see you with my TV set ♪

07:23.590 --> 07:27.129
♪ Oh, baby, I see you with my TV set ♪

07:27.164 --> 07:30.496
♪ I cut your head off,
I put it on my TV set ♪

07:30.607 --> 07:33.933
♪ I use your eyeballs
for knobs on my TV set ♪

07:34.005 --> 07:35.616
♪ I watch TV ♪

07:35.681 --> 07:37.314
♪ I watch TV ♪

07:37.371 --> 07:41.138
♪ Oh, baby, I see you with my TV set ♪

07:41.215 --> 07:42.370
Deran: Let's get 'em!

07:42.405 --> 07:45.011
♪ Yeah, baby, I hear you on my radio ♪

07:45.149 --> 07:47.344
Baz: Your loss, buddy!

07:47.415 --> 07:50.880
♪ You know I flip, flip, flip,
flip, flip for your radio ♪

07:50.915 --> 07:54.431
♪ You're gonna drip,
drip, drip on my radio ♪

07:54.466 --> 07:57.876
♪ A.M. radio, P.M. radio ♪

07:57.911 --> 08:00.960
♪ Since I tuned you inside my radio ♪

08:00.995 --> 08:02.428
♪ Like this ♪

08:12.616 --> 08:15.674
[Laughter]

08:15.676 --> 08:17.559
[Laughing] I'm sorry.

08:17.606 --> 08:19.506
Here.

08:19.561 --> 08:20.810
Shoot him, Pope.

08:20.857 --> 08:24.249
Deran: Come on. Shoot me in the face.

08:24.389 --> 08:25.818
Shoot him! Shoot me in the face!

08:25.820 --> 08:27.349
I'm giving you a free shot.

08:27.384 --> 08:28.954
[Laughing] Sorry.

08:28.956 --> 08:30.356
Come on, Pope.

08:30.358 --> 08:31.824
♪ I watch TV ♪

08:34.903 --> 08:37.429
Oh, come on! That's a new gun.

08:37.688 --> 08:39.722
[Cellphone chimes]

08:41.167 --> 08:43.469
Oh, you wanna... Oh, ho ho!

08:45.213 --> 08:46.852
Cutback.

08:46.911 --> 08:48.945
Give me your phones. Smurf's been arrested.

08:49.010 --> 08:50.608
Uh, get the passport, get Craig here,

08:50.643 --> 08:51.942
- and then start shredding.
- Yeah, yeah. How much?

08:51.977 --> 08:53.567
Everything! J, give me your phone, too.

08:53.602 --> 08:55.410
I gotta change out the SIM card.

08:55.445 --> 08:56.849
[Cellphone chimes]

08:56.884 --> 08:58.417
[Inhales]

09:09.596 --> 09:11.797
Shit, Renn. I-I gotta go.

09:11.799 --> 09:12.798
Shit!

09:14.501 --> 09:15.934
I gotta go.

09:18.545 --> 09:20.538
- Pope: Just like that?
- Yeah. Put everything in the truck.

09:20.619 --> 09:21.912
Leaving town tells them we're guilty.

09:21.947 --> 09:23.647
- Yeah, we <i>are.</i>
- [Motorcycle engine revs]

09:26.308 --> 09:27.646
In, in, in.

09:27.648 --> 09:29.391
Hey, Craig, give Deran a hand inside

09:29.426 --> 09:31.405
and get the cash behind the dryer, okay?

09:31.499 --> 09:34.219
I'm gonna call you when
we get to the safe house.

09:34.307 --> 09:37.489
- Pope: What?
- You said we shouldn't run, so don't run.

09:37.491 --> 09:39.391
- Hey, get in.
- Y-You're taking <i>him?</i>

09:39.474 --> 09:41.942
I know that you're not gonna roll
on us if the cops squeeze you.

09:41.977 --> 09:43.686
- Him, I'm not so sure of.
- Baz, I don't have a passport.

09:43.721 --> 09:45.029
Okay, well, we'll figure it out.

09:45.064 --> 09:46.729
Get in the car!

09:47.686 --> 09:50.086
Like hell you're leaving me behind.

09:59.712 --> 10:02.414
[Engine starts]

10:02.416 --> 10:04.416
[Tires squealing]

10:13.326 --> 10:15.294
[Tires screech]

10:19.566 --> 10:21.433
[Engines turn off]

10:32.579 --> 10:33.979
Baz: Let's go.

10:35.806 --> 10:37.573
J, put the food there.

10:42.175 --> 10:44.343
- What happened? What went wrong?
- Just relax.

10:44.398 --> 10:45.363
We're just gonna sit tight,

10:45.398 --> 10:47.270
wait for the lawyer to
call, then we're home-free.

10:47.305 --> 10:50.127
- So, what... Venezuela?
- Yeah, buddy, Venezuela.

10:50.174 --> 10:52.097
I'm not the one that screwed
up the watch store recon.

10:52.099 --> 10:53.985
- So you're just gonna have to...
- I told you we should have taken out

10:54.020 --> 10:55.331
those tweakers.

10:55.370 --> 10:56.702
If the tweakers could have I.D.'d anyone,

10:56.785 --> 11:00.038
the cops would have picked
<i>us</i> up, not Smurf.

11:00.115 --> 11:01.429
Are you gonna call her?

11:01.464 --> 11:05.244
Yeah, I'm gonna ring up Oceanside
PD and ask if Smurf's available.

11:05.308 --> 11:06.941
Catherine.

11:11.317 --> 11:13.974
After we cross the border,
I will call Catherine.

11:14.027 --> 11:15.460
Okay?

11:15.556 --> 11:17.789
[Vehicle approaches]

11:21.862 --> 11:23.231
Hey.

11:30.492 --> 11:32.259
Down. Get down. Get down.

11:33.258 --> 11:35.225
[Banging on door]

11:39.749 --> 11:41.914
[Banging on door]

11:42.018 --> 11:43.265
Smurf: Open up.

11:43.344 --> 11:45.605
And try not to shoot me.

11:59.635 --> 12:01.703
You bring the passports?

12:02.538 --> 12:04.139
Craig: Cops let you out?

12:04.826 --> 12:06.558
She was never in.

12:06.617 --> 12:09.217
So, this was what... some kind of test?

12:10.912 --> 12:13.946
I'll take the keys to Chula Vista, please.

12:15.804 --> 12:17.572
Cash.

12:22.359 --> 12:24.260
This feels light.

12:24.556 --> 12:27.288
Someone must have dipped into it.

12:27.521 --> 12:29.828
How do you expect to get
to South America on this?

12:29.867 --> 12:32.583
- I didn't touch the money.
- It's your responsibility.

12:32.618 --> 12:35.509
You put us through all this for nothing?!

12:36.170 --> 12:39.300
Hey, what happened to not taking risks?

12:40.627 --> 12:45.569
You are running bullshit
jobs behind my back!

12:45.604 --> 12:48.113
Now, that's what I call a risk!

12:48.216 --> 12:50.550
We are not running <i>any</i> jobs.

12:52.592 --> 12:55.387
I'm gonna give you an
opportunity to come clean.

12:55.476 --> 12:57.893
Someone better tell the truth.

13:09.699 --> 13:11.257
There'll be no next job.

13:11.312 --> 13:13.005
Craig: We're gonna stop working?

13:13.007 --> 13:14.906
Not me... <i>you.</i>

13:15.008 --> 13:17.376
No more money. You're on your own.

13:17.378 --> 13:18.377
Deran: What?!

13:18.572 --> 13:20.124
This conversation is over.

13:20.171 --> 13:21.376
That's bullshit! What
are we supposed to do?!

13:21.434 --> 13:24.868
This conversation is over!

13:34.527 --> 13:36.428
[Door opens]

13:48.308 --> 13:51.310
[Door creaks, closes]

13:51.312 --> 13:55.331
Do you think what I said was
only meant for <i>them?</i>

13:55.366 --> 13:57.967
[Chuckles]

13:58.085 --> 14:00.675
I didn't do anything behind your back.

14:01.972 --> 14:05.090
Put this shit back where it belongs.

14:13.700 --> 14:14.943
Where were you?

14:14.978 --> 14:17.139
I had to copy my history
homework from Kristy Peters,

14:17.230 --> 14:19.031
and she can barely spell her name.

14:19.066 --> 14:21.166
[Chuckles]

14:21.233 --> 14:22.466
Are you okay?

14:22.788 --> 14:24.431
Yeah, I just had a weird morning.

14:24.466 --> 14:25.714
[Chuckles]

14:26.775 --> 14:28.267
This'll help.

14:29.199 --> 14:31.399
[School bell rings]

14:41.369 --> 14:43.411
Okay?

14:43.413 --> 14:45.740
What do 4-year-olds
like to eat?

14:45.797 --> 14:47.163
What?

14:47.384 --> 14:48.986
Well, you have a younger brother.

14:49.076 --> 14:51.610
I don't know... Play-Doh? [Chuckles]

14:51.715 --> 14:53.715
I can't believe you haven't noticed.

14:53.750 --> 14:55.341
Where did you find it?

14:55.758 --> 14:57.858
It must have fallen in my bag.

14:57.993 --> 15:00.160
You didn't tell me it was your mom's.

15:02.024 --> 15:04.725
Yeah, well, that's no big deal.

15:04.844 --> 15:06.778
Yes, it is.

15:12.306 --> 15:14.407
I'll never take it off again.

15:17.546 --> 15:19.530
Just don't wear it to the house.

15:19.595 --> 15:21.862
Smurf and my mom, they, uh...

15:21.933 --> 15:24.667
They had a falling-out. It
might drudge up some old shit.

15:24.723 --> 15:25.979
Okay.

15:27.099 --> 15:28.231
Gimme it.

15:30.453 --> 15:33.088
J. You missed my class.

15:40.046 --> 15:41.613
Whose is this?

15:43.335 --> 15:45.442
Well, it didn't smoke <i>itself.</i>

15:46.172 --> 15:47.605
It's mine.

15:49.143 --> 15:50.810
Nicky, you can go.

15:53.334 --> 15:55.295
<i>Now,</i> Nicky.

16:12.610 --> 16:14.684
[Engines turn off]

16:14.719 --> 16:16.861
What do you think Smurf knows?

16:16.896 --> 16:19.349
I don't know, man. I wouldn't
let it get to your head, though.

16:19.384 --> 16:21.351
She says she knows.

16:21.455 --> 16:23.153
Yeah, well, what's there to know?

16:23.244 --> 16:25.355
Nothing.

16:25.357 --> 16:27.056
This one's yours, man.

16:27.222 --> 16:29.222
I didn't put a hole in it.

16:32.966 --> 16:34.632
It was a one-time thing.

16:34.667 --> 16:37.150
So, what is going on with you?

16:37.310 --> 16:39.499
Does your grandmother know you smoke pot?

16:39.534 --> 16:41.988
What, are you gonna kick me out of school?

16:41.990 --> 16:43.497
No.

16:44.332 --> 16:46.664
You're too smart to be a dropout.

16:47.765 --> 16:49.095
Lighter?

16:49.519 --> 16:51.292
Come on. Give me your lighter.

16:55.527 --> 16:57.194
[Scoffs]

17:09.933 --> 17:13.219
You surf, right, J?

17:13.348 --> 17:14.835
Sometimes.

17:16.124 --> 17:19.326
A photographer I like is
doing an exhibit in Carlsbad.

17:19.486 --> 17:21.094
Surf photos.

17:21.400 --> 17:22.465
Want to go?

17:50.124 --> 17:51.191
What?

17:53.352 --> 17:55.273
You bring something up from Mexico?

17:55.366 --> 17:57.397
No.

17:57.399 --> 17:58.900
Coke or meth?

17:58.935 --> 18:00.994
Do I look like I sell meth?

18:01.117 --> 18:02.065
Coke it is.

18:02.100 --> 18:04.058
How much did you clear?

18:06.841 --> 18:08.575
8!

18:08.787 --> 18:10.156
That's it?

18:10.444 --> 18:11.604
We cleared 12.5.

18:11.716 --> 18:12.701
You guys did a job?

18:12.787 --> 18:14.581
Us and the kid.

18:15.124 --> 18:16.541
You lied to my face!

18:16.576 --> 18:18.418
Yeah, what about all the bullshit
you were telling <i>me</i> before?

18:18.453 --> 18:20.387
Wait a sec! You're
telling me J got a piece?!

18:20.446 --> 18:22.852
- He didn't cut and run.
- I didn't run, okay?

18:22.887 --> 18:26.066
I could have sworn that was <i>your</i>
ass going in the other direction.

18:26.136 --> 18:27.260
Why didn't you cut me in?!

18:27.323 --> 18:30.010
- 'Cause you were in Mexico, you idiot.
- Well, wait a goddamn day!

18:30.045 --> 18:31.423
Hey!

18:31.458 --> 18:33.458
Where's my cut of the coke?!

18:33.833 --> 18:34.868
Not here!

18:34.870 --> 18:37.170
[Both grunting]

18:40.427 --> 18:41.333
Aaah!

18:41.368 --> 18:43.969
Pope: Way to go, genius!
You let him get away!

18:44.179 --> 18:45.745
Whoo-hoo!

18:46.140 --> 18:48.114
Whoo! Whoo! Aah!

18:48.116 --> 18:50.445
♪ I love you, I hate
you, I'm on the fence ♪

18:50.480 --> 18:52.704
♪ It all depends whether
I'm up, I'm down ♪

18:52.739 --> 18:55.260
♪ I'm on the mend,
transcended on the hour ♪

18:55.295 --> 18:58.124
♪ I like you, despise you, admire you ♪

18:58.433 --> 19:00.369
Deran: Let go of me, man!

19:00.404 --> 19:03.616
Baz: You've been out for a month,
and you risk everything for 12 grand?!

19:03.663 --> 19:06.366
Oh, what about you?
Drugs across the border?

19:06.368 --> 19:07.700
Yeah, no risk there.

19:07.702 --> 19:08.812
You should have come to me first!

19:08.847 --> 19:10.251
I gotta run everything by you now?

19:10.286 --> 19:11.504
- Is that how it works?
- Yeah!

19:11.506 --> 19:13.314
Since you went away, yes.

19:13.393 --> 19:17.768
Are you really mad that I did a job
or is it that I cleared more than you?

19:17.803 --> 19:19.770
I'll see you on the ground.

19:22.804 --> 19:24.425
♪ Tell me all he says to you ♪

19:24.506 --> 19:27.346
♪ I promise to exploit you ♪

19:29.964 --> 19:33.317
♪
Ah-h-h-h-h-h-h-h ♪

19:33.394 --> 19:34.840
♪ Put me on a pedestal ♪

19:34.875 --> 19:37.943
♪ But I'll only disappoint you ♪

19:40.346 --> 19:41.980
♪ Tell me all he says to you ♪

19:42.015 --> 19:44.788
♪ I promise to exploit you ♪

19:47.634 --> 19:49.021
♪ Give me all your money ♪

19:49.056 --> 19:51.110
♪ And I'll make some origami, honey ♪

19:51.112 --> 19:52.612
[Rapid beeping]

19:52.614 --> 19:54.482
- Ooh, I got you!
- Let go of me!

19:54.677 --> 19:56.059
♪ I think you're a jerk ♪

19:56.155 --> 20:02.747
♪ But others find you
very fu-u-u-u-u-nny ♪

20:02.782 --> 20:04.991
[Beeping continues]

20:13.168 --> 20:14.974
J's not here, sweetie.

20:15.080 --> 20:16.069
Yeah, I figured I'd wait.

20:16.153 --> 20:18.231
I wanted to thank him for something.

20:19.277 --> 20:22.312
Wouldn't you be more
comfortable waiting by the pool?

20:23.908 --> 20:25.475
Yeah.

20:26.666 --> 20:28.233
[Car door unlocks]

20:30.264 --> 20:31.564
Thank you.

20:50.671 --> 20:52.639
Hey, is Baz here?

20:52.686 --> 20:55.453
No. He's not back yet.

20:55.709 --> 20:59.144
I, uh... I got some food for Lena,

20:59.179 --> 21:01.112
'cause I heard you weren't feeling well.

21:03.634 --> 21:05.301
Baz said.

21:08.441 --> 21:11.361
Why didn't you go with the guys
to celebrate Pope's birthday?

21:15.466 --> 21:16.596
What's in the bag?

21:16.598 --> 21:18.687
Stuff for mac and cheese.

21:19.601 --> 21:21.067
Come in.

21:29.922 --> 21:32.691
[Door opens, closes]

21:56.070 --> 21:57.870
[Sighs]

22:32.550 --> 22:34.651
[Tires screech]

22:37.845 --> 22:39.412
[Engine turns off]

22:47.266 --> 22:48.588
[Knocks] Yo!

22:48.902 --> 22:50.223
You in?

22:58.728 --> 23:00.054
Renn?

23:01.540 --> 23:02.845
You here?

23:03.992 --> 23:05.525
It's Craig.

23:09.243 --> 23:10.417
Oh, shit!

23:10.490 --> 23:12.080
Hey! Hey!

23:12.602 --> 23:14.917
Hey, wake up. Hey! Hey!

23:14.952 --> 23:15.818
Oh, no!

23:15.872 --> 23:17.374
Hey. [Smacks leg]

23:17.444 --> 23:19.244
Hey. Hey. Wake up.

23:19.279 --> 23:20.319
Yo.

23:20.367 --> 23:21.667
Renn?

23:23.259 --> 23:25.190
Hey. Come on.

23:31.084 --> 23:32.265
Oh, God.

23:32.267 --> 23:34.267
[Breathing heavily]

23:37.846 --> 23:40.248
[Rock music plays]

23:46.129 --> 23:49.048
♪ Well, he took them a hammer ♪

23:49.349 --> 23:52.085
♪ And he took them a nail ♪

23:52.491 --> 23:55.768
♪ And they gave you no ransom ♪

23:55.893 --> 23:58.958
♪ And they sent you no bail ♪

23:59.146 --> 24:02.228
♪ With no view of a heaven ♪

24:02.377 --> 24:05.737
♪ Yeah, they gave you their hell ♪

24:06.401 --> 24:07.934
♪ Yeah ♪

24:07.936 --> 24:12.755
♪♪

24:15.851 --> 24:17.229
[Sighs]

24:17.264 --> 24:20.219
- Oh.
- That smells good.

24:20.458 --> 24:21.892
Yeah, it's the only thing I can make.

24:22.004 --> 24:23.571
Um, where?

24:25.036 --> 24:26.968
Yeah, it's like two cheeses.

24:27.007 --> 24:29.043
Costs about 3 bucks.

24:29.097 --> 24:30.929
My mom really liked it. [Chuckles]

24:31.304 --> 24:32.631
Today must be hard.

24:32.920 --> 24:34.933
It's your mom's birthday, too, right?

24:35.013 --> 24:36.213
Yeah.

24:38.715 --> 24:40.739
Yeah, it's weird.

24:41.091 --> 24:43.236
No one even talks about her. It's...

24:45.002 --> 24:46.712
It's like she never existed.

24:46.952 --> 24:48.847
Yeah.

24:49.028 --> 24:50.461
That's Smurf.

24:53.051 --> 24:54.319
Did you know my mom?

24:54.747 --> 24:55.754
A little.

24:55.833 --> 24:58.133
What about her and Baz?
Were <i>they</i> close?

25:00.858 --> 25:02.867
He tried to get her help.

25:04.378 --> 25:07.466
And it looked like she might
turn the corner a couple times.

25:08.603 --> 25:10.811
Then the money started disappearing.

25:11.342 --> 25:14.273
Couple hundred here or
there, and then a lot more.

25:14.450 --> 25:16.844
And they just... they had to change locks.

25:17.701 --> 25:21.671
Yeah, she said that Smurf kicked
her out because she stood up to her.

25:22.194 --> 25:24.870
Said Smurf turns on
anyone she can't control.

25:26.097 --> 25:28.053
Or goes against her.

25:28.292 --> 25:30.556
Is it ready yet?

25:30.651 --> 25:31.650
Ask J.

25:33.323 --> 25:35.177
- [Chuckling] Go ahead.
- [Chuckles]

25:35.212 --> 25:36.303
Yay!

25:36.338 --> 25:38.841
- [Chuckles] Yay!
- Yum!

25:38.928 --> 25:39.988
Catherine, where's your bathroom?

25:40.023 --> 25:42.083
- Around the corner.
- Thanks.

25:53.713 --> 25:56.648
So, what was it, uh, you
wanted to thanks J for?

25:56.650 --> 25:58.198
[Chuckles]

25:58.233 --> 26:01.433
We got busted for smoking pot at school.

26:02.160 --> 26:03.854
He said it was his. [Chuckles]

26:03.930 --> 26:05.783
- Such a good boy.
- [Door opens]

26:05.837 --> 26:08.371
Oh, I have a great pot
hookup if you ever want some.

26:08.406 --> 26:09.169
- Do you really?
- [Door closes]

26:09.204 --> 26:10.677
Yeah. For sure. Anytime.

26:10.712 --> 26:12.431
- Sure.
- Yeah.

26:12.466 --> 26:14.733
Craig?

26:14.735 --> 26:17.102
Are you okay, sweetheart?

26:25.868 --> 26:27.612
[Sighs]

26:32.451 --> 26:34.619
[Exhales sharply]

26:37.056 --> 26:38.957
[Grunts]

27:10.756 --> 27:14.259
[Cellphone beeps, ringing]

27:14.316 --> 27:15.499
Woman: <i>Emergency room.</i>

27:15.534 --> 27:17.495
Yeah, I'm trying to find someone.

27:17.497 --> 27:18.969
A Ray Blackwell.

27:19.004 --> 27:20.567
<i>Blackwell?</i>

27:20.602 --> 27:21.633
Yeah.

27:21.635 --> 27:24.013
<i>Checking.</i>

27:24.048 --> 27:25.723
<i>No one by that name
has been admitted.</i>

27:25.833 --> 27:27.360
Yeah, he's not gonna have I.D. on him.

27:27.407 --> 27:30.646
He's a white male in his 60s.

27:30.681 --> 27:31.874
Probably reeks like alcohol.

27:31.909 --> 27:33.400
Can you check again, please?

27:33.449 --> 27:34.848
<i>You are...?</i>

27:37.010 --> 27:38.647
His son.

27:38.682 --> 27:39.948
<i>One moment.</i>

27:42.036 --> 27:44.972
<i>No one by that description
has been admitted.</i>

27:45.092 --> 27:46.563
Okay, thank you.

27:52.498 --> 27:53.995
[Sliding door opens]

27:54.078 --> 27:55.244
Hey.

27:56.275 --> 27:57.447
I gotta talk to you.

27:57.482 --> 27:59.350
- Daddy!
- Hey, sweetie.

27:59.411 --> 28:01.151
Ricardo called. The rent's past due.

28:01.186 --> 28:03.009
Well, I don't have it.
We're laying low. I mean...

28:03.044 --> 28:05.211
Oh, okay, I'll tell him that.
I'm sure he'll understand.

28:05.392 --> 28:08.747
Well, it wouldn't be an issue if we
just lived in one of Smurf's buildings.

28:09.256 --> 28:10.482
[Laughs]

28:10.585 --> 28:13.056
Just ask him if he can let it
slide a few more days, please.

28:13.116 --> 28:15.202
But you can dig up the money
to blow on Pope's birthday.

28:15.237 --> 28:16.309
Cath...

28:17.257 --> 28:18.569
I already caught it from Smurf.

28:18.604 --> 28:20.546
I really don't want to hear
it from <i>you,</i> too.

28:20.581 --> 28:22.284
Oh, just ask <i>her</i> for it.

28:22.948 --> 28:26.104
Doesn't help that I have to keep making
excuses for why you won't bring Lena over.

28:26.139 --> 28:27.799
Can I have more?

28:27.801 --> 28:30.001
J makes it better than you.

28:30.003 --> 28:31.537
What...

28:31.572 --> 28:33.272
J?

28:33.340 --> 28:35.407
He brought the mac and cheese.

28:35.409 --> 28:37.086
[Scoffs] What?

28:37.137 --> 28:38.853
He's in the bathroom.

28:47.593 --> 28:49.154
What are you doing here, man?

28:49.240 --> 28:50.557
Is that my mom?

28:50.624 --> 28:52.020
Did Smurf send you?

28:52.859 --> 28:54.718
- What?
- To find out if Cath is really sick.

28:54.767 --> 28:56.563
Did Smurf send you?

28:56.644 --> 28:58.213
No.

28:58.281 --> 29:00.882
I thought I told you to come to me.

29:00.930 --> 29:02.923
The job with Pope and Deran.

29:02.993 --> 29:04.769
You should have talked
to me about it first.

29:04.848 --> 29:06.381
I'm sorry.

29:07.861 --> 29:09.974
You can't just be coming around here, man.

29:09.976 --> 29:12.474
This is <i>my</i> house.

29:12.531 --> 29:14.264
<i>My</i> family.

29:15.448 --> 29:16.983
I'll go.

29:26.811 --> 29:28.313
It's his mom's birthday.

29:28.358 --> 29:30.239
Not just Pope's.

29:40.622 --> 29:42.647
Smurf takes my child without asking,

29:42.682 --> 29:44.042
and you want me to apologize?

29:44.077 --> 29:45.598
You said shit you shouldn't have said!

29:45.633 --> 29:46.961
No, I should have hit her with the car!

29:46.996 --> 29:48.310
Okay.

29:48.418 --> 29:50.785
Do it for <i>me,</i> then,
please. Just do it for me.

29:50.843 --> 29:52.158
Screw... you.

29:52.238 --> 29:53.804
Okay.

29:53.978 --> 29:56.933
- Stand up for me.
- Cath, fix it.

29:56.990 --> 29:58.642
Fix it!

30:07.580 --> 30:09.381
What is going on with you?

30:11.734 --> 30:12.857
Nothing.

30:12.930 --> 30:13.996
Bullshit!

30:16.512 --> 30:18.180
Smurf's icing me out.

30:19.755 --> 30:21.404
Why didn't you say something?

30:21.493 --> 30:23.299
'Cause I'm trying to handle it.

30:29.858 --> 30:31.042
I messed up.

30:31.667 --> 30:32.944
The cop?

30:33.410 --> 30:35.007
[Sighs]

30:36.018 --> 30:38.461
Just feel like shit's
getting out of control.

30:50.100 --> 30:53.171
Smurf will get over it. She needs you.

30:53.733 --> 30:55.176
Call her.

30:55.996 --> 30:59.131
- Baz, I can't.
- Cath, you gotta call her.

31:00.229 --> 31:02.296
You gotta make things right.

31:04.810 --> 31:07.119
I would like to make a toast.

31:08.267 --> 31:11.370
I'm so happy that we can
finally all be together

31:11.439 --> 31:17.754
to celebrate the day I first laid
eyes on my beautiful, beautiful boy.

31:19.011 --> 31:21.379
Here's to my firstborn.

31:22.879 --> 31:24.522
- Pope.
- Pope.

31:31.301 --> 31:33.736
Make a wish and blow out your candle.

31:37.585 --> 31:39.544
It's not just Pope's birthday.

31:40.202 --> 31:41.848
It's my mom's, too.

31:49.155 --> 31:50.755
Yes, it is.

31:52.403 --> 31:54.671
Pope, blow out your candle.

32:02.919 --> 32:04.487
Who wants cake?

32:07.379 --> 32:10.032
[Dance music plays]

32:10.067 --> 32:13.435
[Men cheering, whooping]

32:16.485 --> 32:17.867
Excuse me, can we get some girls over here?

32:17.902 --> 32:19.793
- Sure.
- To Pope.

32:20.824 --> 32:22.182
- Pope.
- Pope.

32:22.279 --> 32:23.429
Pope.

32:27.584 --> 32:29.453
I think Smurf knows about the jobs.

32:29.488 --> 32:30.757
- Relax.
- I told you... She's bluffing.

32:30.803 --> 32:31.769
How do you know that?

32:31.830 --> 32:33.530
Did anyone say anything?

32:33.658 --> 32:35.814
We stick together and our mouths shut,

32:35.868 --> 32:37.311
she won't know shit.

32:37.349 --> 32:40.043
Hey, can we not talk about our
mom in the strip club right now?

32:40.091 --> 32:41.503
Thank you.

32:43.765 --> 32:45.733
Woman: Hey, guys. Dance?

32:45.937 --> 32:49.724
Yeah, hey, J, what do you
like... brunette or redhead?

32:50.208 --> 32:52.991
Doesn't matter. They're both
for <i>me</i> anyway. [Laughter]

32:53.119 --> 32:55.119
Hey, which girl here give a good time?

32:55.534 --> 32:57.898
- Pepper.
- Pepper!

32:57.933 --> 32:59.226
Pepper?!

33:02.316 --> 33:03.734
You want a dance?

33:03.769 --> 33:04.847
Yeah.

33:04.920 --> 33:06.628
For my man, J.

33:06.761 --> 33:09.233
- No, he's kidding.
- No, I'm not.

33:09.268 --> 33:12.565
- Give him the ride of his life.
- I have a girlfriend.

33:12.600 --> 33:13.584
You're cute.

33:13.651 --> 33:15.687
Hear that? Thinks you're cute, bro.

33:15.722 --> 33:17.822
Don't hurt her feelings, okay?

33:21.849 --> 33:23.383
Thank you.

33:24.925 --> 33:26.535
So, is this Pope?

33:26.570 --> 33:27.962
Baz: That is Pope.

33:28.713 --> 33:30.012
Welcome home, soldier.

33:30.101 --> 33:33.813
I was telling her about that classified
shit you were doing in Afghanistan.

33:34.415 --> 33:35.942
She wants to thank you for your service.

33:35.977 --> 33:38.338
Yeah, I wasn't in Afghanistan, so...

33:38.377 --> 33:41.081
[Chuckles] I don't care, honey.

33:41.152 --> 33:45.294
He paid me $1,000 to put a smile
on your face, so you coming or what?

33:53.005 --> 33:54.840
[Cellphone ringing]

33:59.654 --> 34:01.888
[Ringing continues]

34:04.407 --> 34:05.538
[Cellphone beeps]

34:07.241 --> 34:08.717
Who's this?

34:08.719 --> 34:10.553
<i>It's me... Renn.</i>

34:11.426 --> 34:13.054
- Uh...
- [Bottle clanks]

34:13.130 --> 34:14.896
W-What's up? Where are you?

34:15.295 --> 34:16.594
<i>The E.R.</i>

34:16.652 --> 34:18.202
<i>Can you come?</i>

34:19.094 --> 34:21.964
Uh, yeah, I'll... I'll be right there.

34:22.733 --> 34:23.899
[Cellphone beeps]

34:25.203 --> 34:26.597
Out.

34:32.619 --> 34:34.320
Sit down.

34:45.413 --> 34:47.080
You can touch me.

34:54.795 --> 34:56.252
Stay right here.

35:03.187 --> 35:05.798
Can't remember the last
time I had an erection.

35:05.866 --> 35:07.499
So...

35:07.611 --> 35:10.079
- I can fix that.
- I don't think so.

35:11.118 --> 35:12.623
Try me.

35:15.881 --> 35:17.587
Stand over there.

35:24.176 --> 35:25.910
Turn around.

35:34.090 --> 35:36.458
Take off your clothes.

35:48.539 --> 35:50.173
Like this?

35:54.311 --> 35:56.420
I said turn around.

36:06.079 --> 36:07.636
Gotta wear the rubber.

36:10.712 --> 36:13.014
[Inhales sharply]

36:27.732 --> 36:29.060
[Gasps]

36:29.095 --> 36:30.273
Say we can't.

36:30.433 --> 36:32.299
- What?
- "We can't."

36:32.435 --> 36:34.479
- We can't.
- Say it.

36:34.598 --> 36:36.131
We can't.

36:49.112 --> 36:50.920
"We can't, Andrew."

36:51.154 --> 36:53.074
We can't, Andrew.

36:56.534 --> 36:57.867
[Zipper opens]

37:03.266 --> 37:05.197
[Wrapper crinkles]

37:06.427 --> 37:08.247
Say it like you love me.

37:08.525 --> 37:10.599
- We can't, Andrew.
- Mean it.

37:10.634 --> 37:12.320
- We can't, Andrew.
- Mean it.

37:12.358 --> 37:14.268
We can't, Andrew!

37:15.049 --> 37:20.799
♪♪

37:23.339 --> 37:25.307
[Dance music plays]

37:29.494 --> 37:30.856
Where's Deran?

37:30.969 --> 37:32.889
He's in the back, with the girls.

37:35.664 --> 37:36.764
Let's go.

37:37.159 --> 37:38.398
What about Baz?

37:38.433 --> 37:40.233
Screw Baz.

37:40.357 --> 37:41.823
Let's go.

37:49.902 --> 37:52.212
J: S-So, where are we going?

37:52.311 --> 37:56.418
You didn't say <i>anything</i>
to Smurf about that thing we did?

37:56.453 --> 37:58.545
- No.
- [Tires screech]

38:01.275 --> 38:03.561
Pope, I didn't say anything.

38:04.415 --> 38:05.603
Good.

38:07.288 --> 38:08.494
Get out.

38:08.529 --> 38:09.931
[Gearshift cranks]

38:10.277 --> 38:11.676
[Engine shuts off]

38:19.349 --> 38:20.816
[Vehicle door closes]

38:28.617 --> 38:30.507
You read the Bible?

38:30.571 --> 38:31.904
What?

38:33.188 --> 38:35.323
The seven seals.

38:37.126 --> 38:39.594
Only Jesus can open them.

38:41.859 --> 38:46.172
First four unleash the Four
Horsemen of the Apocalypse.

38:48.953 --> 38:51.955
Conquerors bent on conquest.

38:54.543 --> 38:57.712
Do you think that's us?

38:57.714 --> 38:59.447
Who?

38:59.651 --> 39:02.950
Me, Baz, Craig, and Deran.

39:02.952 --> 39:04.318
Four.

39:06.398 --> 39:07.979
I don't think so.

39:08.851 --> 39:11.385
Yeah, probably not.

39:15.593 --> 39:17.393
Over the fence.

39:20.881 --> 39:24.195
Pope, I didn't say anything to Smurf.

39:24.260 --> 39:26.093
Over the fence.

39:35.290 --> 39:36.424
[Sighs]

40:01.009 --> 40:03.474
Pope: You remember where Julia is?

40:04.372 --> 40:07.348
Well, that tree looks familiar.

40:07.540 --> 40:08.984
[Sighs] I thought she was over here,

40:09.074 --> 40:12.473
but I think I took you
to the wrong side, man.

40:35.244 --> 40:38.312
No one even says her name, you know?

40:44.209 --> 40:46.338
Yeah. [Sighs]

41:00.969 --> 41:03.237
She ever talk about me?

41:04.706 --> 41:06.607
Sometimes.

41:12.532 --> 41:14.702
We used to have this thing, you know...

41:16.256 --> 41:18.568
on our birthday...

41:18.607 --> 41:20.663
when we were kids.

41:21.592 --> 41:23.291
You know when you, uh, you make a wish,

41:23.372 --> 41:25.322
you blow out your candles.

41:26.470 --> 41:29.938
After, I'd tell her what my wish
was, and then she'd tell me hers.

41:30.006 --> 41:33.474
We weren't supposed to do that, but...

41:36.321 --> 41:38.655
...it still felt like a secret.

41:39.624 --> 41:40.990
You know?

41:41.164 --> 41:44.066
When it... when it was just us.

41:48.836 --> 41:50.024
Pope...

41:52.188 --> 41:55.323
What about... her and Baz?

41:59.322 --> 42:00.755
What about 'em?

42:02.649 --> 42:04.784
Were they close, too?

42:07.122 --> 42:09.624
Baz has a way of getting what he wants.

42:19.715 --> 42:21.415
I didn't...

42:21.609 --> 42:24.908
I didn't know that she
would never come back.

42:31.426 --> 42:33.294
It's not your fault.

42:35.496 --> 42:38.968
I get why you felt like
you had to kick her out.

42:39.020 --> 42:40.753
Yeah?

42:41.048 --> 42:43.237
Why is that?

42:43.239 --> 42:45.298
Because of the drugs. I mean...

42:47.076 --> 42:48.609
Who told you?

42:50.523 --> 42:52.091
Catherine.

42:56.732 --> 42:58.457
[Exhales deeply]

43:03.771 --> 43:05.339
It's cold.

43:27.570 --> 43:28.846
[Door closes]

43:37.896 --> 43:39.062
Hey.

43:42.764 --> 43:44.175
Where's J?

43:45.568 --> 43:47.035
Must have left with Pope.

43:47.879 --> 43:48.836
[Refrigerator door closes]

43:48.906 --> 43:50.604
It's all good with Cath?

43:50.765 --> 43:52.359
How should <i>I</i> know?

43:53.619 --> 43:55.376
She didn't call you?

43:55.999 --> 43:57.345
[Chuckles]

43:57.347 --> 43:58.813
Nope.

44:08.085 --> 44:10.553
Anyone have anything to say to me?

44:22.586 --> 44:24.104
- [Refrigerator door opens]
- You have your own places.

44:24.150 --> 44:26.205
Why don't you sleep there tonight?

44:28.510 --> 44:29.677
Yeah, right.

44:29.761 --> 44:30.935
Deran.

44:31.822 --> 44:32.480
What?

44:32.567 --> 44:34.687
You're not sleeping here tonight.

44:36.985 --> 44:38.254
[Scoffs]

44:45.037 --> 44:48.089
[Door opens, closes]

44:48.196 --> 44:49.865
What are <i>you</i> waiting for?

44:51.431 --> 44:53.178
Pope pulled a job.

45:02.301 --> 45:03.868
Uh-huh.

45:05.051 --> 45:07.085
With Deran and the kid.

45:09.161 --> 45:10.829
With J?

45:12.496 --> 45:14.622
You didn't know?

45:14.701 --> 45:16.131
What about Craig?

45:17.890 --> 45:20.421
He brought a package back from Mexico.

45:22.038 --> 45:24.864
It was a one-time thing. I
made sure it won't happen again.

45:24.938 --> 45:27.775
You should have made sure it
didn't happen in the first place.

45:27.815 --> 45:29.582
He hid it from me.

45:32.441 --> 45:35.360
Look, I did what you asked.
I came clean about the jobs.

45:35.395 --> 45:36.377
[Door opens]

45:36.504 --> 45:38.779
Hey. You got that joint?

45:38.921 --> 45:40.978
I certainly do.

45:52.397 --> 45:54.693
[Door opens, closes]

45:54.728 --> 45:57.228
[Indistinct talking]

46:01.156 --> 46:02.407
Renn?

46:05.157 --> 46:07.024
- Hey.
- Hey.

46:13.398 --> 46:14.998
What happened?

46:16.165 --> 46:17.679
O.D.'d.

46:19.054 --> 46:21.387
Debbie from next door found me.

46:23.213 --> 46:24.806
I got ripped off.

46:25.335 --> 46:27.719
The coke and the pills.

46:27.754 --> 46:30.931
Bastard even took the
necklace I got in Bali.

46:31.345 --> 46:33.963
Just... left me there.

46:35.347 --> 46:36.994
You know who?

46:41.144 --> 46:43.370
Well, the important thing is you're okay.

46:47.461 --> 46:50.423
I'm gonna find out who did this to me.

46:52.293 --> 46:53.988
And you're gonna get him.

46:54.169 --> 46:55.689
What?

46:55.926 --> 46:57.724
You hurt him.

46:58.715 --> 47:01.328
I will make it worth your while.

47:05.412 --> 47:07.195
Just rest, okay?

47:08.637 --> 47:09.970
Yeah.

47:17.400 --> 47:18.671
[Door closes]

47:28.221 --> 47:30.502
Smurf: Aren't you gonna
come kiss me good night?

47:39.048 --> 47:40.734
Nicky stayed over.

47:41.105 --> 47:42.650
I told her she could.

47:42.748 --> 47:44.411
You don't mind, do you?

47:46.723 --> 47:47.976
Come.

47:59.832 --> 48:01.974
I made something for you.

48:09.022 --> 48:10.527
You know, this morning, you told me

48:10.581 --> 48:13.829
the boys didn't do anything behind my back.

48:14.888 --> 48:17.022
That isn't true, is it?

48:18.868 --> 48:20.386
[Chuckles]

48:20.453 --> 48:22.748
You're a good liar, kiddo.

48:23.264 --> 48:25.365
I didn't expect that.

48:27.573 --> 48:30.453
But you are your mother's son, huh?

48:32.645 --> 48:35.184
You know the mistake I made with her?

48:36.093 --> 48:38.646
I gave her too many chances.

48:50.773 --> 48:53.061
Don't ever lie to me again.

48:58.566 --> 49:01.101
♪♪

